Montreal Gangs

2024-04-17

1. Data

Network representing relationships between gangs, obtained from Montreal Polices central intelligence database, spanning 2004 to 2007. Nodes are gangs, and an edge represents some kind of relationship between two gangs (as elicited from interviews with gang members).

data <- read.csv("montreal/MONTREALGANG.csv", header = TRUE, row.names = 1)

adj_matrix <- as.matrix(data)
net <- graph_from_adjacency_matrix(adj_matrix, mode = "max", weighted = TRUE, diag = FALSE)
plot(net, layout = layout_nicely(net))

2. Node centrality

degree_centrality <- degree(net)
nodes_size <- 10 + 10 * degree_centrality / max(degree_centrality)
plot(net, layout = layout_nicely(net), vertex.size=nodes_size)

3. Degree distribution

degree_distr = degree_distribution(net)
hist(
  degree_centrality, 
  breaks = 20, 
  col = "skyblue", 
  main = "Degree Distribution", 
  xlab = "Degree", 
  ylab = "Frequency"
)

4. Longest path in net

diamenter_path = get_diameter(net)

ecol <- rep("gray80", ecount(net))
ecol[E(net, path=diamenter_path)] <- "orange" 

ew <- rep(2, ecount(net))
ew[diamenter_path] <- 4

vcol <- rep("gray40", vcount(net))
vcol[diamenter_path] <- "gold"

plot(net, 
   vertex.color=vcol, 
   edge.color=ecol, 
   edge.width=ew, 
   edge.arrow.mode=0,
   layout = layout.fruchterman.reingold
)

5. Communities

clp <- cluster_label_prop(net)
plot(clp, net)
